##A grass-roots community grid worker's job description during the outbreak

Micro-signal Jianjiaobuluo

Function description, pepper tribe, amplify your voice! Chinese Women Workers Exclusive Information Platform, you are welcome to pay attention!

ABSTRACT: to fight the epidemic, as a grass-roots community in Chengdu, a full-time Grid, since the Spring Festival work. See a family of five back from Wuhan active isolation; security uncle is not respected... Hear 4 aunties that do not wear a mask to play Mahjong as usual; middle-aged man does not cooperate to measure a body temperature, still park car in the gate of small area... ...

My name is Chen Hong, a grass-roots community in Chengdu, a full-time Grid, 35 years old this year. In the fight against this epidemic, I, like the rest of the community, have been working since the New Year's Eve, and have not had a day off.

One
As a full-time grid worker in the community, there is a lot of work to be done, especially during the holidays.
Before New Year's Eve, I and the members of the two committees of the community had visited more than 50 families in our jurisdiction, including retired Party members, veteran cadres, help recipients and Shidu families, and sent them holiday gifts and condolence money.
It was supposed to be a good rest during the Spring Festival, but there was a new outbreak of pneumonia, and it spread faster than expected. Therefore, our community leaders also in accordance with the requirements of the higher authorities, began to combat the epidemic work deployment arrangements.
On January 23, I was having lunch when I got a call from the community secretary telling me to start working overtime on New Year's Eve. I put down the chopsticks and thought, maybe this is a battle against the new coronavirus, we have to be ready to fight a long war.
The community has divided me and a member of the two committees, Yang Lijun (I call her sister Yang) , into a small group, which is mainly responsible for more than 700 households in four units in the community under its jurisdiction and related work.
Our work during the epidemic period is mainly as follows: checking the residents in the area under our jurisdiction every day; calling the residents in the area to find out the situation; putting up the government leaflets for the corridor and the residents in the area every day; counting the people who come and go in the area; Dissuade people from wearing masks and so on.
Sister Yang is putting up notices
Household screening is a very complicated and repetitive task. The two of us have now checked more than 700 households in the district four times. Every day there is a different situation, we'll check every day and report back in time that afternoon.
Yang and I will go to the household statistics
Some of the residents are at home and actively cooperating with our work is fine, so the work will go well. However, some residents knocked several times but could not open the door, did not answer the phone, we do not know what the situation is, so will go to these households again and again to continue to knock on the door, continue to search.
Of course, we always ask at the door of the households, and take the initiative to keep them at a distance of more than one meter. Even when enthusiastic residents offered us a glass of water, we politely declined.
When we called to check whether residents had gone out during the Spring Festival and whether they had been to places where the epidemic was serious, the vast majority of residents and residents cooperated with us by telling us their whereabouts these days, let us feel grateful for their support of our work.
On January 28, I met a family of five who had come back from Wuhan. After they returned home, they volunteered to report to our community, and the family was quarantined at home for 14 days.
During this period, the family bought food in advance for Three Meals a Day, and took their own temperature every day and sent it to us on time. If there are things that need help from the community, such as picking up the express, taking out the garbage, etc. , they will call us and we will send someone to help them in time.
After the family was quarantined for 14 days, the medical service and I went to their house, took everyone's temperature, found no fever and other symptoms, and lifted the quarantine.
Community health workers go to homes to take temperatures

Two
Of course, during this period, some of the residents were not so cooperative. We can not quarrel with such residents, and we can not use strong words. We must also persuade them to cooperate with our work.
Last week, a middle-aged man was driving back from Chengdu. When he arrived at the gate of our community, the security guard was going to take his temperature. As a result, he refused to cooperate and said to the security guard, "who are you to take my temperature? " The Security Guard listened, still patiently persuaded: "This is our job, please cooperate! " As a result, the middle-aged man has been swearing.
The security guard took the temperature of the people coming in and out of the compound
Because this person is not cooperate, security does not open the door to let him into the community, two people are frozen there.
Then this security guard called me, and I called 911 right away. When the two policemen arrived, he dutifully took his temperature.
It seems that some people are only "wearing a big cap" uncle, on our ordinary security uncle disdain, this is really chilling!
We went to the house and knocked on the door a dozen times and made a dozen phone calls, but no one answered the door or answered the phone. We couldn't think of anything to do except go to his house three times a day, morning, noon and night, keep knocking on the door, keep making phone calls. Oh! THINK OF IT as exercise!

Three
Because we are in charge of a community is an open community, the front door and back door can be free access. So, this time in order to facilitate the registration of people in and out, our community and property company personnel together to block the front and back doors of the community, but also the middle of the unit also added two doors closed.
The middle passage of the housing estate was blocked
Starting from February 7, our community began to enter and exit personnel issued cards, each household is a person one card, and is the real name system, the name on the card is written by our community and property staff.
Although we have a lot of work to write our names on the cards, by registering and issuing cards with real names, we can effectively confirm the information of the floating and resident population in the community, and at the same time ensure that residents can enter and leave the community with one card per person, it also protects the health and safety of the residents.
Our community and volunteer team members in the door-to-door to give everyone cards, we took the opportunity to remind residents to go out as little as possible, so that more residents attention to the epidemic, attention to their own health.
If a relative of the community visits, we will tell them the policy, dissuade them from visiting relatives at this time, because increased the risk of virus infection.
When these policies are being discussed, some people cooperate actively while others do not listen to reason. At this point, we let the families living in the community to come out and dissuade them, let them know in the current epidemic situation, stay at home is the safest.
In order to carry out the work in an orderly manner, our community also mobilized community residents as volunteers, let them with us to take the temperature of outsiders, statistics in and out of the personnel situation.
The volunteers are counting the information
Among the volunteers were party members, retired workers and young people going to university. They take turns to volunteer every day before they go about their business. During this period, we divide the work, some in the front door statisticians, some in the back door statistics vehicles, some to the people in and out of the body temperature, and sometimes too busy to drink water.
The first two days, we are not accustomed to go out with a card, so there will be forget to take the card by security and volunteers forced to go back to pick up the card things.
February 9 at 3:00 p.m. , a resident went out without a card to the supermarket shopping, when I happened to be on duty at the door, I persuaded him to go home to pick up the card. He saw my sincerity, smiling at us, he said, "you have worked so hard one by one to persuade, explain, remind, so that we can all feel at ease! I will go back to pick up the card right away, do not cause any trouble to you! " Then he trotted back to pick up the card.
Seeing his fat body running, I secretly laughed and secretly rejoiced.
A retired volunteer uncle sees our community members doing the same job over and over again and patiently explaining policies and job requirements to residents every day, smile and say to us: "You are really hard! The community work is really meticulous! This time with you to do something for the neighbors, I feel special value! "
Every time I hear these words, my heart is warm, feel their work has a sense of accomplishment.
In fact, my husband is one of our community volunteers, he said to see me every day out early and late, must use practical action to support me.
He volunteered for two hours a week in the morning, and in the afternoon he cooked for me and the kids. I now go home and eat ready-made food every day. And because I walk more than 20,000 steps every day, back home already waist leg is weak, my husband in the evening to give me massage shoulder neck and leg, I am also quite embarrassed.
Alas, what can be done? I wonder how long the work will last!

Four
My district is the new elevator apartment district, property staff and security is relatively young, most of the staff are middle-aged and young people, relatively easy to manage.
And some old courtyard and resettlement community, most of the residents are the elderly, so, the work of community staff will be more difficult, community workload will be more.
I have a good girlfriend who is a grid worker in another community. She and I work very similar every day, but she is responsible for the community is the resettlement community, the community has a lot of elderly people.
We also talk about the day's work every day, especially when it comes to the residents of the neighborhood who don't listen to reason, and we vent and comfort each other.
Slogans to fight the epidemic in the community
Last week, I heard her say, four old aunts in their 70s were playing Mahjong at the door of a unit in her neighborhood, and none of them were wearing masks. When she saw it during the inspection, she went up to them and advised them that at this very moment, the government does not allow playing Mahjong, asking them to cooperate and put away the Mahjong table.
As a result, one of the AUNTIES, who usually looks very kind, said aloud that day: "old are all old, dead calculate! "
Hearing this, my friends said they did not know how to answer the words, so kindly advised them to take the Mahjong table, or call security to remove the table.
The four old aunts saw her serious expression and reluctantly withdrew from the table. But the next day, my friend in another unit of the stairs inspection, and saw them a few old aunt around a table playing Mahjong, or did not wear a mask.
The aunties saw her coming and quickly said, "we'll remove the bench right away. Don't worry, WE WON'T GIVE ANY TROUBLE TO THE GOVERNMENT! ".
The other day my friend said something even more irritating.
It was a few days ago, the community began to enter the personnel and vehicles for registration and temperature, a middle-aged man drove to the community gate, my friend said foreign vehicles are not allowed to enter the community, to register, to staff temperature.
As a result, the middle-aged man ignored my friend's words, did not cooperate with the temperature, but also directly deliberately parked the car in front of the community, get out of the car also hard to close the door and left. As a result, my friend quickly contacted the property and security of the community and called the tow company, which later towed the car away.
The middle-aged man came back, see his car is gone and shouted abuse, my friends they several community staff listened, also do not talk to him, also ignore him.

Five
The working hours in our community are 9 to 5, but Yang and I hardly ever leave at 5:00 on the dot, because after every day's work, we have to go back to the office and report the work situation that day before we can leave, and if you find a problem, fix it.
During this period, because I can not take care of the home, my husband does all the housework every day, and my daughter also studies and does homework at home.
The outbreak, my daughter in the training institutions of the winter vacation classes were canceled, the teacher suggested online classes, and my daughter is only the second grade of primary school, for fear that the children online classes have no effect, I did not agree, at home to give her a reading, writing diary and so on.
The other day I saw her diary content is: "during the Spring Festival, my mother goes to the community work every day, no time to play with me, but I can watch cartoons, watch "little Prince" , "journey to the West" , still can draw, play with toys. I want to go to the park to play, want to go to the zoo to see monkeys and elephants, but my mother said that now is a very special period, not allowed to go out, out of the country is to make trouble. I don't know what a crisis is, but I do know that listening to your mother is a good boy..."
See such words, I am very happy, for the daughter of sensible and gratified.
Since the Lunar New Year's Eve, my colleagues and I have been working continuously for more than half a month. In addition to doing a good job of epidemic prevention, we also need to do a good job of screening for potential safety hazards during the holidays, as well as the health of the district supervision and inspection, regular supervision of the property staff to the district's elevators, handrails, trash cans and other places disinfection.
In the past half month, together with Yang Jie and the volunteers, we have posted and printed more than 4,000 notices to more than 700 households, taken the temperature of dozens of people, and reported more than a dozen reports statistically.
Volunteers hand out flyers to residents
The last few days were the Lantern Festival. By rights, after the Lantern Festival, the year will be over. However, I am very concerned to see the increasing number of infections and suspected infections in the daily dynamics of the epidemic, also hope that through their work can reduce the scope of the spread of the virus for the country's early relief of an epidemic to make a contribution.

Six
"No noise, no traffic, seven in the evening, like three in the morning. Wuhan, like being hit the pause button. Lively, hidden by the virus, everyone and everyone are far apart. How long before you can take off your mask and ask face-to-face, "have you eaten? "
That night, when I saw the text in the video, my tears came down.
Wuhan was shut down because of the pneumonia epidemic. Countless parents, in order to fight the epidemic, wrote a letter of invitation, to Wuhan; Countless Lovers, friends, because of the sudden epidemic, separated by two places.
These two days heard that we have increased a few confirmed cases here, I feel even more can not take it lightly.
As a community of ordinary staff, I sincerely hope that the residents can seriously cooperate with our work, do not visit chat pile up, do not say the weather is good want to go out in the sun. Because when you're in the sun, the virus is in the Sun.
If you have to go out to buy things must wear a mask, the temperature on the body temperature, do not add to our work, do not add to social chaos.
State regulations say stay at home, don't go out. Staying at home is the biggest contribution you can make to the country right now, because the home that you find boring is the very home of the health care workers fighting the epidemic and the people who have to work outside, you can't go home if you want to.
"epidemic is the order, prevention and control is the responsibility. ". As grass-roots staff, we have the responsibility, also have the obligation to do their own work, although we will be wronged in the work, but we still do not flinch. The fight against the epidemic is a matter not only for the people of Wuhan but also for the people of the whole country. We must unite as one and unite as one to win the battle against the epidemic.
I hear the Cherry Blossoms in Wuhan are very beautiful. When the warm season of Cherry Blossom in Wuhan, when the City Press "play key" again, I must go to Wuhan with my family to enjoy the beauty of spring, enjoy the fragrance of flowers.
I look forward to that day.
(Note: Both Chen Hong and Yang Lijun are pseudonyms.)
